    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\nI've studied the existing patterns in `server.js`, `server.d.ts`, and `user-agent.ts`. The `next/geo` module will follow them exactly.\n\n### Files to create (4) + 1 to modify\n\n**1. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** — Core implementation\n- `Geo` interface with 7 optional string fields\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` map for 10 country codes (US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA)\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers): Geo` — reads Vercel headers (`x-vercel-ip-*`), falls back to `cf-ipcountry` for countryCode, derives `country` from the map\n- `geo({ headers }): Geo` — thin wrapper (mirrors `userAgent`)\n- `isInRegion(geo, regions)` — case-insensitive countryCode membership check\n- `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2)` — Haversine formula returning km\n- No external dependencies; `?? undefined` converts `null` from `headers.get()` to `undefined` for strict-mode safety\n\n**2. `packages/next/geo.js`** — CJS entry point using the exact dual-export pattern from `server.js`: build an exports object, assign to `module.exports`, then re-assign each named export via `exports.xxx`\n\n**3. `packages/next/geo.d.ts`** — Re-exports from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo` using `export type { Geo }` for the interface and plain `export { ... }` for functions (mirrors `server.d.ts`)\n\n**4. `packages/next/package.json`** — Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` in the `files` array (g sorts after f)\n\n**5. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** — 7 test groups using only Node.js `assert`: Vercel headers, Cloudflare fallback, Vercel-over-Cloudflare priority, isInRegion matching/non-matching/case-insensitive/missing, Haversine NY→London ~5570km ±50km, all-undefined when no headers, all 10 country codes have names\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types          # type-check\npnpm --filter=next build          # build\nnode -e \"const g = require('./packages/next/geo.js'); console.log(Object.keys(g))\"\n# → [ 'geo', 'geoFromHeaders', 'isInRegion', 'geoDistance' ]\npnpm test-unit                    # no regressions\n```",
